Dominic Howard shares &quot;We went to see <a href="http://www.last.fm/music/Skrillex" class="bbcode_artist">Skrillex</a> in Camden around October. We went, 'Fuck, it's so heavy,' loved it. I was like a full metal gig, they had circles of death, people were moshing, I hadn't seen a reaction like that to electronic music before. We took inspiration and came up with '<a title="Muse &ndash; The 2nd Law: Unsustainable" href="http://www.last.fm/music/Muse/_/The+2nd+Law:+Unsustainable" class="bbcode_track">The 2nd Law: Unsustainable</a>'.&quot;

 &quot;Some of that hard dubstep and brostep coming from America, is capturing the imagination,&quot; singer Matt Bellamy adds. &quot;The moshpit has moved from guitars and gone towards the laptop, so with that song we're trying to see if we can challenge the laptop. We created something that was dubsteppy but we wanted to see if we could do it with real instruments. We wanted to ask, 'Can rock bands compete with what these guys are doing?'&quot;

